{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba6a964c-1ae5-4737-affe-41084cb7717c","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_6G2tKSzwqivNKc23Ec4hKC","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3c733792436442508d1b4e600d85cc8a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-3c733792436442508d1b4e600d85cc8a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"5aa79513-4822-4e33-93b0-3eae5c7e7f78","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n3. `Program.fs` (listed last) — opens both\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the compile order. The fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"1C4B:1521D2:B07C5C:CD55D0:69F3FA12"},"id":"4d3644ff-d5f7-4d64-903d-df4aa0d0c4e4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:54.437Z","parentId":"9160a5ff-9c30-4f8c-bb67-5f63eecdb732"}
